<p>You're unlikely to use over 200MB a month if you don't use the browser a lot. However, if you find yourself actually using the phone beyond talking for any large amount of time you'll want to evaluate at that time. An application on the iPhone can be small at around 10MB and much larger 300-500MB range, if you download it OTA (Over the air) you would have hit your limit already. That aside, it really all depends on how you are going to use it.&nbsp;</p>